Explanation2:
\begin{aligned}
&\text{For 7th term $\left(T_7\right)$, Put $r=6$.}\\
&\Rightarrow \quad T_7=T_{6+1}={ }^9 C_6\left(\frac{4 x}{5}\right)^{9-6}\left(-\frac{5}{2 x}\right)^6 \\
&\Rightarrow \quad T_7=\frac{9 \times 8 \times 7}{3 !}\left(\frac{4}{5}\right)^3 x^3\left(-\frac{5}{2}\right)^6 \frac{1}{x^6} \\ 
&\Rightarrow \quad T_7=\frac{9 \times 8 \times 7}{3!}5^3\frac{1}{x^3} \\
&\Rightarrow \quad T_7=\frac{10500}{x^3}
\end{aligned}
